                    <msItem n="4" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_7_4">
                        <locus from="132" to="191">Column 1, lines 132-191</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against Barya and Legewon, containing the legend of St. Susenyos and Warzelya</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Column 1, line 132</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, barya are a people believed to serve the demon or spirit provoking epilepsy and therefore barya is identified with this disease. Legewon is a name for Satan, chief of the barya and 
