                    <msItem n="9" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_7_9">
                        <locus from="114" to="141">Column 2, lines 114-141</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against blacksmiths, Barya, Legewon, chest pain, rheumatism, migraine, colic, zar, tegrida, methat afafta and pleurisy</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Column 2, line 114</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, barya are a people believed to serve the demon or spirit provoking epilepsy and therefore barya is identified with this disease. Legewon is a name for Satan, 
                            chief of the barya and one of the most frequently occurring devils in Ethiopic magical literature. Zar is a spirit not considered as a demon. Tegrida is a devil who stays in lonely places 
                            and causes epilepsy. Methat is a violent disease with fever which kills quickly (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>
                    </msItem>
                    
                    <msItem n="10" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_7_10">
                        <locus from="142" to="241">Column 2, lines 142</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against the evil spirit, for people possessed by buda and barya, against <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->, sorcerers and magical actions, against 
                            barya, legewon, chest pain, rheumatism, migraine, colic, <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> and <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->.</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line </locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                       
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, buda is a being whose main feature is the evil eye and who possesses people by drinking their blood and eating their flesh. Barya are a people believed to serve the 
                            demon or spirit provoking epilepsy and therefore barya is identified with this disease. <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> is an evil being. Legewon is a name for Satan, 
                            chief of the barya and one of the most frequently occurring devils in Ethiopic magical literature. <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> is very strong colic. <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing--> 
                            is a sorcerer who makes people ill using philtres and poisons (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>

                    </msItem>
